$interpreted: Tindoiimu: We're here. This is the way to the entrance of the Udumbara.
Tingko: Is that the barrier? How are we supposed to enter?
Tindoiimu: This is the key.
Tindoiimu: Did it! Now I just have to close it up from the inside.
Tindoiimu: Wait, what's wrong!?
Tingko: Look, the barrier isn't closing!
Tingko: Is it broken? What's going on?
Tindoiimu: Is it because the Dream Flower was destroyed?
Tingko: The Dream Flower?
Tindoiimu: This pendant should only be held by someone who passed the trials of the Dream Flower, but it was destroyed...
Tindoiimu: And yet no one's been in here for the past few days, but now that I opened it, it broke?
Tingko: Doesn't that mean this barrier is useless, now?
Tindoiimu: We can only hide inside and hope for the best, now.
Tingko: Wow, so this is the protector of the East Alliance...
Tindoiimu: The Udumbara...
Tingko: I'm so proud of you, Princess. You're finally here!
Tindoiimu: Finally here...?
Tingko: You can destroy it now, and then we'll be free!
Tingko: This is it, the culmination of your hatred, the revenge you've always wanted! Redemption for the Insect Tribe!
Tindoiimu: Redemption... in the midst of such chaos...
Maeok: Because you... are the arbiter... Leader of both sides...
Toyokuni: Don't worry, I'll convince them to come save you!
Tindoiimu: Can you call that redemption?
Tindoiimu: But no, this is my goal... this is what I've always wanted.
Tindoiimu: Everything the Insect Tribe has endured...!
Soohyeon: I wish the Alliance were full of people like you, not them...
Soohyeon: You're a good person, I know you are... Why become just like them?
Tindoiimu: Because I want vengeance. I want to kill you all!
Tindoiimu: Payback... for everything...
Juan-Yun: I will protect the Insect Tribe, if you protect the citizens of this Alliance.
Tindoiimu: ......!!!
Nigel: Now I see the responsibilities of being a leader far outweigh revenge and dignity!
Nigel: It's being a beacon for the downtrodden, the unwanted... and helping them find a way to live on!
Juan-Yun: ...You were born into the Alliance... grew up in the Alliance...
Juan-Yun: If you spend time somewhere, and leave a piece of yourself there... that's home enough.
Tindoiimu: I... I want...
???: Where is your home? What do you truly desire?
Tindoiimu: I─
Tindoiimu: I want everyone to live... a good life...
Tingko: Princess! What's wrong with you!? Princess!!
Tindoiimu: ...We can't destroy the Udumbara.
Tindoiimu: If we do, the Insect Tribe will never find redemption. Both sides will be doomed.
Tingko: What are you talking about!?
Tindoiimu: The Udumbara is the backbone of the Alliance's entire belief system. If we destroy it, there will only be unending chaos.
Tindoiimu: And without a common enemy, the Insect Tribe will only turn in on itself.
Tindoiimu: Everything will be engulfed in chaos... a constant cycle of recycled revenge.
Tindoiimu: Everyone... will die.
Tingko: ...Princess, even if everyone dies, I'll be here with you!
Tindoiimu: Tingko, you've changed, don't you realize that?
Tingko: Me?
Tindoiimu: The old you would never speak so carelessly, so callously about death.
Tingko: That's...
Tindoiimu: I've already gotten Juan-Yun killed, I won't hurt you, too. I want you to have a good life.
Tingko: But then... you want us to abandon our plans for revenge? Forgive those beasts?
Tindoiimu: No, that's not what I'm saying. I'm simply saying I see now what is more important.
Tingko: T-Then what do you want us to do!? The rest of the Alliance will never let us live!
Tindoiimu: We have options. We have the Komainu, and Atlas...
Tingko: Options...
Tindoiimu: That's right. But for now, we just have to stay here until Toyokuni comes back with help. I'll make sure you're safe, Tingko.
Tingko: Princess...
Tingko: Okay... I'll listen to you. Let's do our best to find a good life.
???: So, you couldn't do it after all.
Juan-Yun: Sorry I'm late~
